## 6. Build Config Decision

Use **two configs** in `helpers/build.ts`:

| Entry | Config | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| `src/index.ts` | `createAdapterConfig` (CJS + ESM + types) | Standard library pattern used by `client-generator-ts`, `client-generator-js`, etc. |
| `src/bin.ts` | Custom single CJS config with `banner: { js: '#!/usr/bin/env node' }`, `emitTypes: false` | Only needs CJS (Node subprocess). No ESM, no `.d.ts`. Shebang must be the literal first line. |

The bin config uses `bundle: true` so it is self-contained (no `node_modules` needed at runtime when invoked as a subprocess). All dependencies are regular deps in `package.json`, so esbuild marks them external by default via `getProjectExternals`. For the bin, override that by either:
- Setting `bundle: true` and passing `external: []` (or omitting it so esbuild inlines only `@prisma/generator-helper` deps), OR
- Keeping external deps as-is and relying on them being installed alongside the package.

The safer approach for a subprocess generator is to keep deps external (since they will always be installed together in the monorepo / npm package), which is the default behavior.

