## 1. Scalar Type Mapping Table

This mapping is used in `generateTypes.ts` and `generateModel.ts` when converting DMMF field types to TypeScript types.

| Prisma scalar (`field.type`) | TypeScript type |
|---|---|
| `String` | `string` |
| `Boolean` | `boolean` |
| `Int` | `number` |
| `Float` | `number` |
| `BigInt` | `bigint` |
| `Decimal` | `string` (serialized as string to avoid precision loss) |
| `DateTime` | `string` (ISO-8601; use `Date` only as a comment note) |
| `Json` | `unknown` |
| `Bytes` | `string` (base-64 encoded) |
| `Unsupported` | `never` |
| Any other (relation/object) | Use the model name as-is (e.g., `User`) |
| Any enum | Use the enum name as-is (e.g., `Role`) |

The mapping function signature:

```typescript
// packages/rest-client-generator/src/typeMap.ts
export function prismaScalarToTs(prismaType: string): string
```

---

## 2. Route Path Derivation

Model name → route path: lowercase the name, then naively pluralize by appending `s` (or `es` for names ending in `s`, `x`, `z`, `ch`, `sh`). Since there is no approved `pluralize` dependency in this new package yet, implement a minimal inline pluralizer rather than pulling in the `pluralize` npm package (which is already a dep of `client-generator-ts` — but we explicitly want a minimal dep tree here).

Algorithm:

```
User      → /users
Post      → /posts
Category  → /categorys   ← acceptable for a REST stub generator; note below
```

A more complete rule set (inline, no dep):

```
ends with 's'|'x'|'z'    → append 'es'   (e.g. Box → boxes)
ends with 'ch'|'sh'       → append 'es'   (e.g. Witch → witches)
ends with 'y' (not vowel) → replace 'y' with 'ies'  (e.g. Category → categories)
everything else            → append 's'
```

Function:

```typescript
// src/utils.ts
export function modelNameToRoute(modelName: string): string
// "User"     → "users"
// "Category" → "categories"
// "Box"      → "boxes"
```

