## 5. The One File to Modify: `tsconfig.build.bundle.json`

Add one entry to the `"paths"` object in `/tsconfig.build.bundle.json`:

```json
"@prisma/rest-client-generator": ["./packages/rest-client-generator/src"],
```

Insert it alphabetically after `"@prisma/param-graph-builder"` and before `"@prisma/query-plan-executor"` (following the existing ordering). The full modified paths block gains exactly that one line.

**Why this file and not `tsconfig.build.regular.json`?** Because the package uses `adapterConfig` (bundled mode), which means it relies on `tsconfig.build.bundle.json` for inter-package source resolution during type-checking in the monorepo. Every package listed in `adapterConfig` is registered here. The root `tsconfig.json` (used for editor tooling) does not need modification because it already uses `"paths"` sourced from `tsconfig.build.bundle.json` via the `"extends"` chain.

Wait — looking at the actual structure again: `tsconfig.build.bundle.json` extends `tsconfig.build.regular.json` and adds `"module": "preserve"` / `"moduleResolution": "bundler"` plus all the `"paths"`. The root `tsconfig.json` extends `tsconfig.utils.typecheck.json`. The `"paths"` live exclusively in `tsconfig.build.bundle.json`. So the one-line addition is:

```json
// In tsconfig.build.bundle.json, inside "compilerOptions.paths":
"@prisma/rest-client-generator": ["./packages/rest-client-generator/src"],
```

